title: Baby Lemonade: 45 RPM
description:
Baby Lemonade was a Scottish band that recorded a handful of songs and disappeared forever. This is shame, because the songs I have been lucky enough to hear... he songs shared with me that I am now sharing with you all   are AWESOME.

Here is their self-titled release (also known as 45 RPM) on Egg Records. It is three songs and five tracks; the last two tracks are demo versions of "Secret Goldfish" and "Real World" that are just.. man, listen for yourself.

I have not found a copy of their LP, One Thousand Secrets, yet, though after 45 RPM  I really, REALLY want to now. I have a feeling it will prolly be a bit of a challenge, as I suspect that it was only ever released on vinyl.
